items.abstract: <jats:p>The influence of metal carbides, TiC, VC, ZrC, Mo<jats:sub>2</jats:sub>C, TaC, and WC, on the liquid-phase oxidation processes of 1-octene by molecular oxygen and <jats:italic>tert</jats:italic>-butyl hydroperoxide was investigated. It was established that vanadium carbide is the most active in the oxidation process of 1-octene by molecular oxygen as well as in the <jats:italic>tert</jats:italic>-butyl hydroperoxide unproductive decomposition process in the hydroperoxide oxidation reaction. It was shown that there is a correlation among the activities of metal carbides in these processes.</jats:p>
title: The Influence of Metal Carbides on the Oxidation Processes of 1-Octene by Molecular Oxygen and tert-Butyl Hydroperoxide
